body:
Maybe this is somehow the wrong repo? but...

I installed the SkiaSharp.SVG 1.60.0 nuget package into a dotnet6 wpf project and trying to load a specific SVG file causes this exception

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2057080/208086551-8904a310-f25c-417c-998f-4058aa29391b.png)

Since it seems to be an XML exception I tried running the SVG through some online XML parserrs and they are all happy. The SVG also renders fine in browsers, and another library is able to load it. Furthermore the Entity that is being reported as missing is clearly defined in the XML on line 63. 

![badcake](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2057080/208087097-e4c5b50c-8e22-4592-990b-f22d152e52dd.svg)


          
**Code**

var    svgSrc    ="C:/Folder/badcake.svg";
var svg  = new SkiaSharp.Extended.Svg.SKSvg();
 var pict = svg.Load(svgSrc);

Since the problem seems to be the call into System.Xml I tried callling that directly like this:
var byteArray = File.ReadAllBytes("C:/Folder/badcake.svg");
using (var stream = new MemoryStream(byteArray))
{
    System.Xml.Linq.XDocument.Load(stream);
}

Which does not produce the exception
